This article is a presidential proclamation by Barack Obama declaring July 27, 2012, as National Korean War Veterans Armistice Day. The proclamation honors all those who served in the Korean War and pays tribute to the brave men and women who lost their lives in the conflict. It recognizes the sacrifices made by American service members and allied forces during the three years of combat in harsh conditions. The proclamation also emphasizes the importance of remembering and honoring the Korean War veterans by upholding the ideals they fought to protect and supporting them with care and respect.